<PaginaIstituzionale lang="en" ogImage="/og/og-chi-siamo.jpg"
  occhiello="The Association"
  titolo="Who we are"
  intro="An epic adventure in the heart of the Valli del Noce: since 2009 we have safeguarded the history, language and traditions of our valleys."
  metaDescription="The El Brenz Historical, Cultural and Linguistic Association, founded on 21 December 2009: projects, partnerships and initiatives for the history and language of the Valli del Noce."
>
  <div class="prosa-istituzionale">
    <p>
      Welcome! You are not here by chance: you have been drawn by the call of an
      association that for over a decade has worked tirelessly to preserve a
      priceless cultural heritage. The <strong>«El Brenz»</strong> Historical,
      Cultural and Linguistic Association, founded on 21 December 2009, is far
      more than a local presence: it is a true engine of initiatives, projects
      and partnerships that have shaped life in the Valli del Noce. Our commitment
      takes the form of concrete actions that breathe new life into local
      history, language and traditions.
    </p>

    <h2>A commitment to culture and language: projects that leave their mark</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>The voices of the past, the poetry of the present.</strong> We
        gave voice to the Rhaeto-Romance tongues with the poetry and music
        competition <a href="/en/os-dal-nos">«Os dal Nos»</a> (our voices). Ever
        since its first edition in 2014, it has inspired artists and poets to
        compose works in <em>Anaunian Ladin</em>, bringing together the different
        linguistic varieties of Val di Non, Val di Sole, Val di Rabbi and Val di
        Pejo. A true hymn to the beauty and identity of our words.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The calendar that tells a story.</strong> With the
        <a href="/en/lunari-dal-nos">«Lunari dal Nos»</a> (our almanacs) project we
        turned a simple calendar into a precious tool for outreach. Each edition
        explores a specific theme, making local history and culture accessible and
        engaging for the younger generations. The 2023 edition, for instance,
        titled «La nosa storia» (our history) and created together with a Basque
        comic artist, was even distributed free of charge in schools.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The documentary that moves you.</strong> After more than two years
        of research, we brought to life the documentary
        <a href="/en/fioi-dal-nos">«Fiöi dal Nos» (children of the Noce), Ladin
        identity of Val di Non and Val di Sole</a>, a deep journey into the
        history and identity of the Anaunian people. This work is not merely a
        film but a legacy we wanted to make available to everyone: we published it
        on our YouTube channel to reach all those who wish to rediscover their
        roots.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>A network of partnerships and recognition</h2>
    <p>
      Our vision does not stop at the valleys. We have woven a dense network of
      partnerships that has earned us recognition and visibility, even in the
      media.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Beyond borders, a bridge between cultures.</strong> We have built
        a bridge to other European linguistic minorities, such as the
        <strong>Catalans</strong> and the <strong>Occitans</strong>, to share
        experiences and reinforce the idea that defending one's identity is a
        value that unites rather than divides. Locally, we work closely with other
        associations and bodies, such as the <strong>Circolo «Al Filò» of
        Denno</strong> and the <strong>«Rezia» Association</strong>, on joint
        initiatives like historical evenings and book presentations, proving that
        there is strength in unity.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Coverage in the press.</strong> Our work has not gone unnoticed.
        Newspapers such as the <strong>«Giornale Trentino»</strong> have reported
        extensively on our initiatives, including the release of the documentary
        «Fiöi dal Nos» on YouTube to make it accessible to all, underlining the
        importance of our research. The magazine <strong>«UnserTirol24»</strong>
        has also given space to our translations and literary contributions, as
        with the poem «L'incanto del bosch», highlighting our work in language
        outreach.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Events for the community.</strong> From dinners on historical and
        linguistic themes to evenings of commemoration, each of our events is a
        chance to meet, learn and share, strengthening community ties and
        celebrating together the richness of our past.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      Become part of our story. Support us by
      <a href="/en/tesseramento">joining as a member</a> or with a donation, so
      that we can continue this extraordinary journey.
    </p>

    <p>
      El Brenz Historical, Cultural and Linguistic Association.
      <strong lang="lld-anau">Raìs fonde no le 'nglacia</strong><br/><em class="text-[#1E2E26]/60">Deep roots do not freeze.</em>
    </p>
  </div>

